snippet.textDisplay: There was actually a good reason why Microsoft skipped Windows 9, a lot of older software took shortcuts to test for the version of Windows it was running on by checking for a 9 in the version info to see if it was running on Windows 95/98/98SE/ME.  In other words, if Microsoft released Windows 9 then a heck of a lot of software used by businesses would suddenly fail to work and, although that would have been a hilarious fail, that isn't something that Microsoft wanted to have happen :\
snippet.textOriginal: There was actually a good reason why Microsoft skipped Windows 9, a lot of older software took shortcuts to test for the version of Windows it was running on by checking for a 9 in the version info to see if it was running on Windows 95/98/98SE/ME.
